#
# labwc environment file. Plain variable=value lines only — labwc parses
# this itself, it does NOT source it as a shell script the way Openbox
# does (see labwc-config(5)). No "export", no quotes needed. Confirmed
# live: with export/quotes in place, QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME ended up in
# every Qt process's real environment as the literal, un-parsed text
# `export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME="qt5ct"` instead of a real value.
#
# qt6ct, not qt5ct: every Qt app actually installed on this system
# (falkon, pavucontrol-qt, pcmanfm-qt) links against Qt6 (confirmed via
# ldd), which can't load the Qt5-only qt5ct platform-theme plugin at
# all — qt5ct theming had been silently inert since the first theme
# (RED) was built, regardless of the export/quotes bug above.
#

# To set your language for displaying messages and time/date formats, use the following:
#LANG=en_CA.UTF8

# To set your keyboard layout, you need to modify your X config:
# http://www.google.com/search?q=how+to+set+keyboard+layout+xorg
QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct
